# Starting a New Project

## Step 1: Clone and Setup
```bash
git clone [this-repo] new-project
cd new-project
pnpm install
```

## Step 2: Extract Tokens from Design

Open `src/styles/globals.css` and update the `@theme` block:

1. **Colours** — Extract from design: primary, secondary, accent, backgrounds
2. **Typography** — Font families (update in both CSS and `<link>` in BaseLayout)
3. **Radii** — Border radius values from the design
4. **Shadows** — Shadow styles if custom ones are needed

```css
@theme {
  --color-primary: oklch(...);
  --color-secondary: oklch(...);
  --font-sans: 'Your Font', system-ui, sans-serif;
  --radius-lg: 0.75rem;
}
```

## Step 3: Review Core Components

Check `src/components/core/` — do any need:
- New variants? → Add to the variant object
- Different defaults? → Update default props
- New components entirely? → Create following the pattern

## Step 4: Build Blocks from Design

Each major section of the design becomes a block in `src/components/blocks/`:

1. Look at the design section
2. Create a new `.astro` file
3. Import core components
4. Define props interface for the content
5. Compose using core components

## Step 5: Compose Pages

Pages in `src/pages/` are pure composition:

```astro
---
import PageLayout from '@/layouts/PageLayout.astro';
import Hero from '@/components/blocks/Hero.astro';
import Features from '@/components/blocks/Features.astro';
---

<PageLayout title="Home" description="...">
  <Hero headline="..." subheadline="..." />
  <Features features={[...]} />
</PageLayout>
```

## Step 6: Handle One-Offs

If something can't fit the token system:
1. Create it in `src/components/custom/`
2. It can use arbitrary Tailwind values
3. Still make it prop-driven and reusable
4. Import into pages alongside blocks

## Checklist Before Shipping

- [ ] All pages have unique titles and descriptions
- [ ] All images use `<Image>` from `astro:assets`
- [ ] All images have `alt`, `width`, `height`
- [ ] No raw colours in core/blocks (only in custom)
- [ ] `pnpm build` passes without errors
- [ ] Test in browser at multiple breakpoints
